string.name: tip_to_open_keyboard
string.b: The keyboard opens any time you touch a text field

string.name: tip_to_view_accents

string.name: tip_to_open_symbols
string.b: Switch to numbers and symbols by touching this key

string.name: tip_to_close_symbols
string.b: Go back to letters by touching this key again

string.name: tip_to_launch_settings
string.b: Touch & hold this key to change keyboard settings, like auto complete

For Voice command to play audio through your Bluetooth headset it must support A2DP and you must have Android OS 2.1 or later.

If your phone sometimes crashes when you disconnect your Bluetooth headset, it is due to a bug in the Android 2.2 OS on certain phones. If you experience this, you can turn off Bluetooth (in Voice command Settings > Advanced)
Voice command can listen for commands and speak back to you through a Bluetooth headset. This works well on most headsets, but there are a few issues you should be aware of.
To be able to speak to Voice command through your headset you must have Android OS 2.2 (Froyo) or later.
